<seg id="7">Dry October for NSW</seg>
<seg id="8">Conditions were more extreme over some of the fire-hit regions to Sydney's west, with Springwood - where many houses were destroyed by fires in October - recording just 5 per cent of its normal rain.</seg>
<seg id="9">Katoomba, in the Blue Mountains, had its warmest October in terms of average maximums in at least 46 years, while its tally of just 6 millimetres of rain for the month was the town's driest on record, Weatherzone said.</seg>
