<seg id="28">Or it could simply be that living in a right-handed world means left-handers get used to fighting for their rights from an early age.</seg>
<seg id="29">The proportion of left-handers in Britain as a whole has risen fourfold in the past 100 years.</seg>
<seg id="30">Around 13 per cent of men and 11 per cent of women are now left-handed, compared to just 3 per cent of those born before 1910.</seg>
