<doc docid="d6bdb35860d2d30d594460ccdf514c85" genre="news" origlang="xx">
<seg id="1">Max Markson has devised a five-point plan to salvage Chris Brown's career</seg>
<seg id="2">Chris Brown in court in 2009 for attacking pop singer Rihanna.</seg>
<seg id="3">Photo: Lori Shepler-Pool/Getty Images Source: Getty Images</seg>
<seg id="4">Celebrity agent Max Markson.</seg>
<seg id="5">Photo: Supplied Source: News Limited</seg>
<seg id="6">WILL Chris Brown ever be able to get his career back on track?</seg>
<seg id="7">The 24-year-old singer once again hit the headlines for all the wrong reasons this week when he checked into rehab for anger management issues.</seg>
<seg id="8">It follows his October 28 arrest for allegedly physically and verbally assaulting a man in Washington.</seg>
<seg id="9">It's just the latest in a long string of incidents that have left Brown's reputation in free-fall, which began when he assaulted Rihanna on the eve of the 2009 Grammy's leaving her bloodied and bruised.</seg>
<seg id="10">So how can a celebrity with such an appalling public persona convince the world to give him another go?</seg>
<seg id="11">Celebrity publicist Max Markson says a simple five-point plan could be the answer to all of Chris Brown's PR problems.</seg>
<seg id="12">Here's what he would advise the Forever singer to do:</seg>
<seg id="13">A tell all interview with Oprah Winfrey: "He needs to come clean and say sorry, just like Lance Armstrong did."</seg>
<seg id="14">Establish a charity: "He needs to prove his remorse through charity work, but he needs to be passionate about it, there's no point doing it otherwise."</seg>
<seg id="15">Organise a charity concert: "He needs to put the hard word on his friends and do an enormous concert for his charity which he should broadcast live around the world to raise a lot of cash."</seg>
<seg id="16">Announce a world tour: "His music is where the strength of his credibility is from."</seg>
<seg id="17">He needs to get back to music and dancing.</seg>
<seg id="18">Write his autobiography: "He should start writing a book to release by next Christmas."</seg>
<seg id="19">He should include what life lessons he's learnt over the past few years.</seg>
</doc>
