<seg id="4">Picture: Michael Klein</seg>
<seg id="5">CARLTON coach Mick Malthouse has adopted a glass half-full approach to Carlton's agonising nine-point loss to St Kilda.</seg>
<seg id="6">The Blues were woeful in the first half at Etihad Stadium and despite being down two men and 33 points at the last change, went within a whisker of toppling the Saints.</seg>
<seg id="7">VIDEO: See Carlton's injury crisis unfold in the player above</seg>
<seg id="8">David Ellard (calf) and Chris Yarran (hamstring) went down to game-ending injuries inside the first 10 minutes, while Michael Jamison was forced to play more than three quarters with a badly damaged shoulder.</seg>
<seg id="9">But so poor were the Blues before a lack of manpower could be a factor, it appeared the injuries masked the real story.</seg>
<seg id="10">Umpire Ray Chamberlain talks with Leigh Montagna after Eddie Betts cleaned up Nathan Wright during the 3rd quarter of the St Kilda vs Carlton match at the Etihad Stadium, Melbourne.</seg>
