<seg id="12">Archibald entries close on Friday and among the South Australian submissions are Riverton artist Robert Hannaford and Andrew Slattery, who has entered his portrait of Australian actor John Jarratt as his Wolf Creek character Mick Taylor.</seg>
<seg id="13">Hannaford has entered with a portrait of historian Bill Gammage, who won the Australian history prize in the Prime Minister's Literary Awards last year with his book The Biggest Estate on Earth: How Aborigines Made Australia.</seg>
